<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Aababba Habib-Vallon Zek</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-01-16 21:10:17</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Ok I'll write a little guide here to help out everyone that wants this amazing little item:<BR>
<BR>
First off, dont attempt this item before level 27, I will explain this later on.<BR>
<BR>
To start, you need to get the severed paw.  This is the paw you have to put the four rings on to get the Paw of Opolla.  The paw can be found in the sewers in North Qeynos.  It is a drop off a level 24 beggar guy named Vin Moltar.  You take a faction hit against Qeynos for killing him but who really cares about just one.  If he is not there, it is annoying because he spawns only once every six hours.  If you really want to dodge the faction hit, give him a rat meat pie.  I just blew his sorry ass up.<BR>
<BR>
Next, you want the silver ring.  Go to blackburrow.  When you first walk in, theres that big pit with all the razorgills at the bottom.  Go camo (they attack no matter what your level is) and take a leap of faith.  The ring is at the bottom of their pool, and its not directly in the middle so search around for a while.  When you get it, put it in the paw (which is a four slot container) and hop the boat to Edruine.<BR>
<BR>
When you get to Edruine, go to tox forest and head to the docks.  If you dont know how to get to the docks, head stright out of Edruine and when you hit the water take a left.  Cant miss it.  Hop the boat or swim over to Kerra isle.  If you go stright out from the docks, the entrance will be on your left, so run that way.  Its a big thing, your not gonna miss that one either.<BR>
<BR>
In Kerra isle (fairly small zone) is High Priestess Mitty (Not Princess Mitty as everyone calls her).  She is fairly easy to find, just look around for a while.  When you do find her, either pull her back to the zone and kill her, or kill all the priestess around her so they wont heal.  The reason you need to be 27+ is so these cats wont train on you.  Mitty will drop the copper ring one out of about 20 times, the silver ring about the same, and the gold ring is VERY rare, 1 out of 100 would be my guess.  She has a spawn rate of twenty miniutes.  <BR>
<BR>
After you kill her and get your copper and gold ring, head to Befallen.  Right when you get in, you will pretty much be standing on where Gynok spawns.  Gynok drops the plat ring.  He drops it at about the same rate as the copper ring, but he is rare as hell, and he wont always spawn.  Things that can spawn in his place are Ice Bone Skele's, Large Rats, Putrid Skele's, Skele's, Ghouls and Dread Bones.  To get Gynok to spawn, kill the things that spawn instead of him.  If you come in and want to start, just sit at the entrance.  Only ONE creature in the entire doungen will be walking around, and that is his place holder.  It will walk down to the third level, then back to the spawn point.  The spawn rate at his point is about half an hour.  When he does spawn, he will be a mummy that is level 22.  Kill him and hopefully get your plat ring.<BR>
<BR>
Hit combine and viola!  Paw of Opolla.  Be prepared to put 60-100 hours into this quest, thats  about the avarage amount of time it will take to do the entire thing unless you get really lucky.</font></td></tr></table>
