<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Grimlikk</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-02-16 20:49:25</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Oddly, this was not a very hard quest to do. In fact the hardest ring for me to get was the silver.<BR>
I never really wanted a Paw but was in befallen at level 24 sitting by the entrance helping a friend when he came running back with an ice boned skeleton, I killed him and continued helping my friend. I was sitting there medding right by entrance when some named mummy hit me, stood up, rooted him, slapped a Envenomed Breath on him, sat back down, he started hitting me again. Killed him he has a plat ring on him. I did an ooc asking what is was for and judging by how many tells I got asking for it I knew it was valuable. Did a little research, decided to do quest. I got a TP to Tox, and spent 6 hours camping Mitty, In the 6 hours she dropped 2 copper rings, and 1 gold ring. Ran to Blackburrow and after 3 hours of auctioning some newbie at Qeynos bank had a silver ring for sale for 4 plat. Ran down, gave Vin a rat pie and 3 kalish, got the container and had my paw. Seeing as I use a 2 handed weapon I traded it to a druid for a chyrsberyl talisman, 2 mith runed bracers, a plat ruby veil, and a totemic helm. <BR>
Not too shabby for level 24.<BR>
BTW at 24 I never had any of the priestess's around Mitty train on me, they did heal her, but I would just pull her away from them.</font></td></tr></table>
